  "dateModified": "2026-04-02",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-02",
  "description": "Cytokinin: a class of plant hormones that promote cell division (cytokinesis) and delay senescence (leaf aging). Synthesized primarily in root tips, transported upward in the xylem, and perceived through a two-component phosphorelay system. The name derives from their role in cytokinesis, though their regulatory functions extend far beyond cell division.",
  "keywords": "botany, plant-physiology, plant-hormones, cell-division",
